    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Symmetrical lens design created in 1866 by Steinheil, which formed the basis for most general-purpose lenses until the early 20th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000020881/International Center of Photography Encyclopedia of Photography (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Symmetrisches Objektiv-Design, 1866 von Steinheil gebaut, das die Grundlage für die meisten Mehrzweck-Objektive bis zum Anfang des 20. Jahrhunderts bildete.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西元1866年，施泰因海爾（Steinheil）創造了對稱式透鏡設計，在西元二十世紀初之前，一般用途之鏡頭普遍以此對稱式結構為基礎。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
